    "updated_at": "2021-08-31T16:25:12Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Would it not make more sense to just not enable the basefee market and have the basefee opcode return zero when there is not a basefee market present?  I don't see the point of enabling the fee market with a static base fee.\r\n\r\nedit: I *do* see the value of being able to handle 1559 (type 2) transactions.  There is a lot of overhead and validation gated on the presence of a basefee market though.  Not the least of which is the 2-stack pending transaction sorter.  \r\n\r\nIs there anything other than the ability to handle type 2 transactions (and a no-op basefee opcode) that we are trying to accomplish with a static basefee config?  ",
